Peter Jennings, the iconic ABC News anchor, revealed his battle with lung cancer, opting for chemotherapy over surgery.
Despite his illness, he remains committed to anchoring "World News Tonight" during treatment.
Colleagues and viewers alike express support and admiration for his courage.
The news industry recognizes his significant impact and enduring legacy.
Jennings' decision to share his diagnosis publicly is seen as a source of inspiration for others facing similar challenges.
His absence from the newscast is felt deeply, but his resilience and determination shine through in the face of adversity.
